SUBJECT: Audit Report - Noida 121 P&C
DESCRIPTION:
I want to inform you that I visited the Noida Sec.121 P&C hub. The devices and infrastructure are in acceptable condition; however, I observed the following issues:

Multiple sockets are damaged and broken.
The caretaker/device operator is not wearing proper footwear and is using formal slippers, which is a risky practice.
The main DB cover is missing. Why do engineers consistently advise against fixing the main DB cover at multiple locations?

SUBJECT: Audit Report - Greater Noida big basket
DESCRIPTION:
I want to inform you that I visited the Greater Noida site today. I have highlighted these issues multiple times and have also addressed them during our safety training. Our first priority should be to check our main DB; however, the engineers are not paying proper attention to this critical point.

Main DB Cover: The main DB cover is missing. The security guard informed me that the engineer advised not installing this cover because, during previous visits, they were focusing on checking the main DB. This situation is very risky and could be harmful for everyone. Please take immediate action to resolve this issue.

Missing Blankers: Many blankers are missing. Please ensure that this is checked and rectified as a priority.

Device Issues: One device is missing its converter and socket.

Your prompt attention to these matters is crucial for maintaining safety at the hub.

Best regards,
[Your Name]

SUBJECT: Audit Report - Mamura sec.66 P&c
DESCRIPTION:
I want to inform you that during my visit to the Mamura Sec.66 P&C hub, I observed that drivers and the caretaker frequently use the MCB switch to turn off the device. This is an improper practice that negatively affects our device uptime. Please instruct the caretaker and the parking owner to refrain from doing this.

Additionally, over the past 3 months, 6 devices have not been used and the connections have already been removed. I had mentioned this in a previous email; however, these devices have not been removed and returned to the warehouse yet. We should not wait until further damage occurs.

Please look into this matter as soon as possible

SUBJECT: Audit Report- Noida sec.67 big basket
DESCRIPTION: I want to bring to your attention that the previously highlighted issue remains unchanged. Our main DB is connected to a sub-meter and the electricity supply for third-party devices (Bolt), which results in our own device usage being very low while most usage is attributed to third-party devices. Please look into this matter.

SUBJECT: Audit Report - Mukundpur P &C
DESCRIPTION:
I want to inform you that I visited the Mykundpur P&C hub. There has been no change in the parking infrastructure condition; it remains very risky and dangerous. I had already informed you in a previous email, but the device has not been repaired yet.

The parking owner mentioned that there is no need for a public charging point, so please change this device to a normal one. Additionally, the fire extinguisher was removed from the wall and stored in the room, which is why the refilling date was not mentioned. Although the inspection personnel collected the fire extinguisher during their round, the parking owner stated that it will be refilled and then re-hung on the wall.
I want to bring to your attention that two new devices were delivered 15 days ago, but they have not been installed yet. Could you please explain the reason for this delay? Additionally, for this hub, we require a 3-pin socket device. Could you clarify why a different model was sent?

SUBJECT: Audit Report - Kalyanpuri P&C
DESCRIPTION:
I want to inform you that I visited the Kalyanpuri P&C hub today. The devices and infrastructure are in acceptable condition. However, I have the following concerns:

The blankers were not fixed during the initial installation, despite my multiple emails regarding this issue.
The main 3-phase wire is exposed, which is very dangerous and risky for everyone.
While fleet members have visited regularly, I am concerned that these safety hazards have not been addressed. Safety is our top priority, and we cannot compromise on this matter.

Please address these issues as soon as possible.
